original: Bjurgert, Anton Hilding Vilhelm, komminister, österökna, f. 13/6/11 i Algutsboda, Kronob. 1., av hemm:äg. Gustaf Viktor Petersson o. Emma Kristina Lindgren. G. 41 m. Josta Andersson. Barn: Lorentz f. 43, Trygve 46. — Stud:ex. i Lund 32, teol. fil. ex. 34, teol. kand. i Lund 38. Kommin. i Ökna sed. 41. Ordf. i kyrkostämma, skolstyr. o. barnav :nd, kassör i skolstyr. o. barnav :nd.
translated: Bjurgert, Anton Hilding Vilhelm, vicar, Österökna, born June 13th, 1911 in Algutsboda, Kronoberg. Son of home owner Gustaf Viktor Petersson and Emma Kristina Lindgren. Married in 1941 to Josta Andersson. Children: Lorentz, born in 1943 and Trygve born in 1946. Anton attended Lund for his studies, graduating high school in 1932, obtaining his degree in theology in 1934, and becoming a candidate of theology in Lund in 1938. He became a vicar in Ökna in 1941. Additionally, he served as the chairman of the church meeting, school board, and child welfare, treasurer of the school board, and child welfare.
